- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper deals with analyzing the quality of self-emerging solutions in congestion games, which is a classic topic in game theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents a general technique for analyzing the quality of solutions in congestion games, which involves formulating the problem as a primal-dual optimization problem. This technique may be of interest to researchers in the field of algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of finding good solutions in congestion games, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the approximation ratio of solutions achieved after a one-round walk starting from the empty strategy profile, which is a topic of interest in machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the quality of non-cooperative solutions in congestion games, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence.
